        <p>nope, but funnily i looked into them a couple of hours ago since they are supported by the u8glib2, which works quite fast on an arduino uno, controlling two oled screens over i2c. (MUCH better and faster then the adafruit library for example) so maybe we could borrow code from there, he also has a font only mode, which omits buffering as yours does i think:</p>

