<blockquote><p>Hi, I added some updated OLED objects.  The new tiar/HW/OLED128x64nice is nice because it will be nicer to other hardware connected to the I2C. (hence with this one, the presence of an factory/i2c/config object is mandatory). If you have two OLEDs connected with different I2C addresses, you can use two  OLED128x64nice objects.  modes:  mode 0: 4 lines of 11 characters (or "bars", see below).  mode 1: 1 line of 11 chars and oscilloscope. mode 2: full height oscilloscope.  <a href="../../uploads/default/original/2X/9/924c2e82a603d217ad080b8cba69aeb55acde3db.png" title="bars2.PNG" rel="nofollow noopener">[image]</a> The tiar/…</p></blockquote></aside>
