      <div class='post' itemprop='articleBody'>
        <p>In case anyone bought this OLED Display:<br><img src="../../uploads/default/original/2X/7/7d73496589cb497a273bb23771a416c841ae47b1.png" width="499" height="442"><br> The default address is 0x3C and it's not a SSD1306, it's a SH1106 <img src="../../images/emoji/twitter/frowningae52.png?v=5" title=":frowning:" class="emoji" alt=":frowning:"></p>

<p>I tested it using the U8G2 library for Arduino on NodeMCU v2 and the SSD1306 definition works but the two first columns are missing and 2 last one are random.</p>

<p>I guess I'll be more careful next time ...</p>

<p><a class="mention" href="../../u/lokki.html">@lokki</a> I didn't find the post you were referring to ^^</p>
